A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Code Section 20-2-310 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
2 student directory information, registering to vote and with selective service, and pledge of
3 allegiance, so as to establish the Jimmy Carter Award for Civic Engagement; to provide for
4 policies and procedures; to provide for related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for
5 other purposes.
6 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
7 SECTION 1.
8 Code Section 20-2-310 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to student
9 directory information, registering to vote and with selective service, and pledge of allegiance,
10 is amended by revising subsection (b) as follows:
11 "(b)(1) Each eligible student in the public schools of this state shall be apprised of his or
12 her right to register as an elector and to vote in elections and of any obligation to register
13 with the Selective Service System. Each eligible student shall be given an opportunity,
14 arranged by the school administration, to register to vote at his or her school during the
15 month of April of each year. The State Board of Education shall promulgate rules and
