16 regulations to carry out this Code section. An excused absence of a student to register or
17 vote, at the discretion of the local unit of administration, shall not exceed one school day.
18 (2)(A) There is established the Jimmy Carter Award for Civic Engagement to
19 recognize public schools at which a high percentage of eligible students are registered
20 to vote. In order to qualify for the Jimmy Carter Award for Civic Engagement, a public
21 school shall meet the following criteria:
22 (i) For a gold level award, 100 percent of eligible students at such public school shall
23 be registered to vote; or
24 (ii) For a silver level award, 85 percent of eligible students at such public school shall
25 be registered to vote.
26 (B) The Department of Education shall develop policies and procedures to recognize
27 public schools which meet the criteria for an award pursuant to this paragraph."
28 SECTION 2.
29 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
